column1:
1. U.S. Citizenship
2. Obtain & maintain a Secret Security clearance
3. Education requirements: https://www.opm.gov/policy-data-oversight/classification-qualifications/general-schedule-qualification-standards/0500/auditing-series-0511/
4. Experience performing a variety of routine taskings in the areas of audit planning, research, scheduling, and coordination
5. Experience gathering and reviewing background information on organizations to be audited to develop an understanding of their programs, structures, policies, objectives, systems, and internal controls
